{
    "lines": [
        {
            "text": "This is a story of four unfortunate men",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "who embarked on a dangerous adventure",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "aboard the ship \"St. Paul and Peter\"",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "at the evening of the 18th century.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Having been forced to live",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "in the easternmost parts of Russia,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "they started a rebellion",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "in which governor Grigorii Nilov was killed,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "they secured a ship",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "and set out to sea.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Each of these men left a record of their voyage,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "but each of them told a wildly different story.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "First, our main hero,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Baron Maurice de Benyovsky.",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "Never truly a baron,",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "his story is that of unlikely adventures",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "and marvels of his command.",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "He claimed to be the sole commander,",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "unwilling slayer of the governor,",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "explorer of Alaska",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "and an amazing diplomat.",
            "image": "B"
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Next up is the Baron's right-hand man,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Ippolit Stepanov.",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "Having travelled through Siberia together,",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "over time they grew apart.",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "In his retelling of the events,",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "Stepanov claimed to be the sole captain,",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "while his \"Hungarian Baron\"",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "was just a thorn in his side.",
            "image": "S"
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Third in this curious set",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "is Ivan Ryumin,",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "who upon reading the diaries of Lord Anson,",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "craved for an adventure of his own.",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "His account is that of wonder and emotion",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "upon witnessing the exotic beauty",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "of the world outside Siberia.",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "Perpetually amazed by his findings,",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "he was never in the center of the story,",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "which made his description of it",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "significantly more objective.",
            "image": "R"
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Last but not least,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "an unfortunate soul",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "by the name of Gerasim Izmailov.",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "Having planned a mutiny",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "to end Benyovsky's command,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "he was abandoned",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "on a deserted island,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "where he lost his mind,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "plotted revenge",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "and was saved one year later.",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "Having obained a ship of his own,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "he set out on the Baron's trail,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "only to learn the hard way",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "that the Japanese shores",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "are a hostile land",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "due to a series of letters",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "dubbed the \"Hanbengoro's Warning\".",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "Having lost hope,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "he explored tha shores of Alaska,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "where now he meets the expedition",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "led by Captain James Cook,",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "with you being the only Russian on board.",
            "image": "I"
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "He asks you for one tiny favor",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "not to him, but to the Motherland",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "and to the Empress Catherine II",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "to enact revenge on the \"Baron\"",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "by making him admit",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "that he's the Hanbengoro.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "The power of his determination",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "sent you on a journey",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "beyond the shores of the mortal coil",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "to take him down",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "in the mystical ship",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "called \"Collective Subconscious\".",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "RED thought bubbles are those you can shoot,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "as well as use as bullets.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "RIGHT-CLICK a red bubble to load it,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "LEFT-CLICK one to shoot it.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "SCROLL to cycle through them.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "The right combination will let you go further.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "There is always one correct argument.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "CTRL will slow down time,",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "while SPACE will speed it up.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Good luck, commander.",
            "image": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Why don't we start with one important question:",
            "image": ""
        }
    ]
  }